# Stack

`TxStack` is a one-dimensional layout primitive for form sections, button groups, compact panel content, and simple vertical or horizontal rhythm.

Reviewed against `packages/tuffex/packages/components/src/stack/src/types.ts`, `TxStack.vue`, and `stack.test.ts`.

## Basic Usage

:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="StackStackDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <template>
    <div style="width: 360px; padding: 16px; border: 1px solid var(--tx-border-color); border-radius: 12px;">
      <TxStack :gap="10">
        <TxButton>One</TxButton>
        <TxButton variant="secondary">Two</TxButton>
        <TxButton variant="ghost">Three</TxButton>
      </TxStack>
    </div>
  </template>
---
:::

## Composition Examples

### Horizontal Actions

```vue
<template>
  <TxStack direction="horizontal" align="center" justify="flex-end" :gap="8" wrap>
    <TxButton variant="ghost">Cancel</TxButton>
    <TxButton variant="primary">Save</TxButton>
  </TxStack>
</template>
```

### Inline Stack

```vue
<template>
  <p>
    Status:
    <TxStack inline direction="horizontal" align="center" gap="0.5rem">
      <TxBadge value="Live" variant="success" />
      <TxTag label="Beta" size="sm" />
    </TxStack>
  </p>
</template>
```

## Interaction Contract

- The root is a `div` with `display: flex` by default.
- `direction="vertical"` maps to `flex-direction: column`; `direction="horizontal"` maps to `row`.
- Numeric `gap` values become px; string values are passed through unchanged.
- `align` and `justify` are passed to CSS variables and then used as `align-items` and `justify-content`.
- `wrap=true` maps to `flex-wrap: wrap`; otherwise `nowrap` is used.
- `inline=true` switches display from `flex` to `inline-flex`.
- The root sets `min-width: 0` so children can shrink inside constrained cards.

## API

### Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| `direction` | `'horizontal' \| 'vertical'` | `'vertical'` | Main axis direction. |
| `gap` | `number \| string` | `12` | Gap between children. Numbers become px. |
| `align` | `string` | `'stretch'` | CSS `align-items` value. |
| `justify` | `string` | `'flex-start'` | CSS `justify-content` value. |
| `wrap` | `boolean` | `false` | Allow children to wrap onto multiple lines. |
| `inline` | `boolean` | `false` | Use `inline-flex` instead of block-level `flex`. |

### Events

| Event | Payload | Description |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| - | - | `TxStack` does not emit custom events. Child components keep their own event behavior. |

### Slots

| Slot | Props | Description |
|------|------|-------------|
| `default` | - | Stack children. |

### CSS Variables

| Variable | Source | Description |
|----------|--------|-------------|
| `--tx-stack-gap` | `gap` | CSS gap. |
| `--tx-stack-align` | `align` | `align-items`. |
| `--tx-stack-justify` | `justify` | `justify-content`. |
| `--tx-stack-direction` | `direction` | Resolved flex direction. |
| `--tx-stack-wrap` | `wrap` | Resolved wrapping mode. |
| `--tx-stack-display` | `inline` | `flex` or `inline-flex`. |

## Best Practices

- Use `TxStack` when the design asks for rhythm between siblings, not for arbitrary page layout.
- Prefer `vertical` for forms and settings panels; prefer `horizontal` for action rows and compact metadata.
- Use `wrap` for button groups that must survive narrow containers.
- Keep `gap` token-based or numeric; avoid using empty children as spacers.
- Use `TxFlex` when you need native flex directions such as `row-reverse` or `column-reverse`.


## Review Notes

- Reviewed against `packages/tuffex/packages/components/src/stack/src/TxStack.vue`, `types.ts`, and `stack.test.ts`.
- Existing tests cover default vertical variables, slot content rendering, horizontal prop mapping, wrapping, inline display, and numeric gap normalization.
- Accessibility note: `TxStack` adds no semantic role. Keep list, form, and navigation semantics on the children or surrounding element.

